plot: Tony fails to reason with Phil as more problems increase with Anthony Jr as his depression worsens.

Phil turns down a compromise in asbestos disposal with Tony. A.J despairs about the world and his future, which drives him to horrible consequences as he goes over the edge. Carmela doesn't know what to do about her son. An affront to Meadow pushes Tony to his limits, and the consequences put the New York and New Jersey families at each others' throats.—Emphinix

After a brief bout of normalcy, AJ has again descended into deep depression worrying his parents and Meadow. He seems to be carrying the weight of the world on his shoulders. His attempt at suicide is unsuccessful thanks to Tony's early arrival home. It lands him in the hospital. After one of Phil Leotardo's men, Coco Cogliano, makes a crude remark to Meadow when she's out for dinner with her new boyfriend, Tony beats him to within an inch of his life. Carmine Lupertazzi's attempt to make the peace falls on deaf ears and Phil refuses to even speak to Tony about the matter. War is in the air.—garykmcd
